OL,7,FHe denied any wrongdoing but was
OL,8,Fcharged with manslaughter after expert
OL,9,Fmedical evidence confirmed Mrs
OL,10,FClaxton's injuries could not have been
OL,11,Fsustained accidentally.
OL,13,FOn Thursday 1 February, a jury found
OL,14,Fhim guilty of manslaughter.
OL,16,FHe has now been sentenced to nine
OL,17,Fyears in prison.
